erritories.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20around%201%20a.m.%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpictures-of-hamas-oct-7-terror-attacks-israeli-homes-photos-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOctober%207%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20arrived%20in%20Amman%2C%20Jordan%2C%20on%20the%20way%20back%20to%20my%20home%20in%20Jerusalem%20from%20a%20trip%20to%20Belfast%2C%20where%20I%20attended%20the%20One%20Young%20World%20Summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20met%20my%20CTO%20at%20the%20airport%3B%20they%20were%20traveling%20to%20Ramallah%2C%20a%20Palestinian%20city%20in%20the%20West%20Bank.%20We'd%20decided%20to%20travel%20together%20to%20the%20borders%2C%20which%20opened%20at%208%20a.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20got%20into%20a%20bus%20that%20was%20supposed%20to%20move%20between%20Jordan%20and%20Israel%20at%20around%208.30%20a.m.%20Then%2C%20we%20were%20told%20they%20were%20closing%20the%20borders.%20We%20started%20checking%20the%20news.%20I%20read%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-hamas-chose-attack-israel-now-after-decades-conflict-gaza-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHamas%20got%20through%20a%20fence%3C%2Fa%3E%20surrounding%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20nervous%20as%20hell%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20you're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-from-river-to-sea-means-israel-palestine-rashida-tlaib-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epro-Palestine%20or%20pro-Israel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20once%20you%20hear%20a%20major%20event%20is%20happening%20in%20the%20region%2C%20you%20know%20what's%20coming%20next%20is%20not%20going%20to%20be%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20got%20off%20the%20bus%20and%20went%20back%20to%20Amman.%20We%20didn't%20know%20what%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20founded%20a%20tech%20startup%20in%20Ramallah%20in%202022%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20born%20in%20Saudi%20Arabia%20but%20grew%20up%20in%20Jordan.%20My%20mom%20is%20from%20Nablus%2C%20a%20city%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20and%20my%20dad%20grew%20up%20in%20Jerusalem.%20I%20moved%20to%20Jerusalem%20at%2016%20and%20went%20to%20university%20in%20Ramallah.%20After%20living%20in%20Qatar%20and%20London%2C%20I%20moved%20back%20to%20Jerusalem%20in%202019%20and%20set%20up%20an%20advertising%20agency%20with%20my%20brother%20in%202020%2C%20which%20I%20was%20a%20part%20of%20until%20January%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202022%2C%20I%20set%20up%20%26quot%3BThe%20Middle%20Frame%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20stock%20image%20platform%2C%20with%20my%20business%20partner%20Raya%2C%20a%20photographer%20I%20met%20in%20Boston%20during%20an%20entrepreneurship%20fellowship%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERaya%20told%20me%20she%20wanted%20to%20build%20a%20platform%20for%20authentic%20stock%20images%20from%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdubai-economic-jewel-of-the-middle-east-gulf-neighbors-saudi-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20the%20Middle%20East%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20North%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20where%20Raya%20was%20coming%20from.%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EBack%20when%20I%20worked%20in%20advertising%2C%20creatives%20always%20struggled%20to%20find%20images%20that%20accurately%20represented%20local%20cultures%20from%20Arab%20regions%20on%20international%20platforms%20like%20Shutterstock%20and%20Getty%20Images.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%201%2C800%20contributors%20are%20signed%20up%20on%20our%20platform.%20Photographers%20upload%20their%20own%20images%2C%20which%20we%20moderate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Palestinian%20startup%20scene%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20business%20is%20based%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frami-kashou-palestinian-fashion-designer-homage-clothing-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERamallah%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20Raya%20lives.%20We're%20both%20familiar%20with%20the%20city%3B%20it's%20where%20I%20went%20to%20university%2C%20and%20half%20of%20my%20family%20lives%20there.%20It%20made%20sense%20cost-wise%20for%20us%20to%20work%20locally%20and%20set%20up%20our%20business%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpalestinian-tech-industry-struggles-amid-israel-hamas-crossfire-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPalestinian%20startup%20community%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20very%20small.%20I%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20around%20the%20world%20don't%20know%20it%20exists.%20It's%20very%20easy%20to%20get%20into%20and%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20good%20environment%20to%20find%20our%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20there%20was%20almost%20no%20political%20and%20economic%20stability%20in%20the%20area%2C%20but%20as%20it%20was%20my%20home%20country%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20to%20try%20and%20do%20my%20part.%20If%20starting%20a%20company%20in%20Ramallah%20could%20benefit%20the%20community%20by%20creating%20jobs%20and%20further%20building%20on%20the%20small%20startup%20scene%20there%2C%20we%20wanted%20to%20try.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20wanted%20to%20onboard%20Palestinian%20team%20members%20to%20give%20them%20experience%20in%20a%20tech%20startup%2C%20but%20we%20had%20been%20struggling%20to%20recruit%20people%20due%20to%20the%20ongoing%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMyself%20and%20Raya%20are%20the%20only%20two%20working%20full-time%20for%20%26quot%3BThe%20Middle%20Frame%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20we%20have%20a%20part-time%20CTO%20and%20web%20developer%20who%20are%20both%20Palestinian%2C%20as%20well%20as%20six%20part-timers%20in%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20stock%20image%20platform%2C%20we%20wanted%20to%20provide%20local%20photographers%20with%20passive%20income%20from%20sharing%20their%20images.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20targeting%20advertising%20agencies%20and%20media%20outlets%20that%20can%20download%20our%20images%2C%20but%20since%20the%20Palestinian%20population%20and%20market%20are%20small%2C%20we%20felt%20there%20was%20a%20limitation%20on%20our%20growth%20and%20scalability.%20Only%20a%20handful%20of%20companies%20and%20publications%20would%20be%20using%20the%20images.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20startup%20community%20is%20also%20small%2C%20there%20aren't%20as%20many%20opportunities%20to%20collaborate%20with%20other%20startups%20or%20gain%20knowledge%20from%20them.%20There's%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthestartupscene.me%2FMenaEcosystems%2FThe-Future-of-Palestinian-Startups%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20VC%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20there%20aren't%20any%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstartupgenome.com%2Fecosystems%2Fpalestine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emature%20startup%20accelerators%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20planned%20to%20expand%20into%20a%20bigger%20market%20eventually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20were%20determined%20to%20keep%20working%20despite%20the%20uncertainties%20caused%20by%20the%20conflict%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20first%20week%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhamas-goal-october-7-attack-israel-gaza-war-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevents%20of%20October%207%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20was%20checking%20the%20news%20every%20day.%20Waking%20up%20was%20a%20struggle.%20People%20living%20in%20Europe%20and%20the%20US%20invited%20me%20to%20healing%20circles%2C%20but%20I%20wasn't%20ready%20to%20talk%20about%20the%20situation%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20October%209%2C%20I%20got%20on%20a%20call%20with%20Raya%2C%20who%20was%20with%20her%20family%20in%20Ramallah%2C%20and%20our%20CTO%2C%20who%20was%20with%20me%20in%20Jordan%2C%20to%20discuss%20the%20next%20steps.%20We%20had%20been%20running%20small%20testing%20advertising%20campaigns%20for%20%26quot%3BThe%20Middle%20Frame%26quot%3B%20and%20were%20supposed%20to%20start%20larger%20campaigns%20in%20October%2C%20but%20we%20decided%20that%2C%20ethically%20speaking%2C%20it%20didn't%20feel%20right.%20We%20stopped%20our%20advertising%20efforts%20until%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20took%20a%20screenshot%20of%20the%20call%20as%20a%20statement%20that%20we%20will%20keep%20working%20even%20in%20the%20toughest%20times.%20When%20%26quot%3BThe%20Middle%20Frame%26quot%3B%20goes%20through%20a%20hard%20time%20in%20the%20future%2C%20we%20can%20look%20back%20at%20that%20screenshot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERaya%20and%20I%20talked%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20her%20moving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-jordan-egypt-say-no-to-refugees-from-gaza-experts-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20Jordan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20she%20said%20it%20wouldn't%20be%20easy%20%E2%80%94%20her%20kids%20and%20husband%20have%20their%20lives%20in%20Ramallah%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20conversation%20didn't%20go%20anywhere%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20thinking%20about%20the%20people%20dying%20and%20the%20struggles%20that%20our%20people%20are%20facing.%20Being%20in%20the%20media%20industry%2C%20we're%20documenting%20life%20in%20the%20region.%20It's%20not%20easy%20for%20us%20to%20ignore%20what's%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20know%20other%20startup%20cofounders%20from%20Gaza%20whose%20office%20buildings%20were%20bombed%20and%20who%20have%20officially%20stopped%20working.%20A%20cofounder%20who%20I%20met%20in%20Jordan%20just%20last%20year%20was%20killed%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20the%20toughest%20news%20I'd%20ever%20received%20in%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe're%20now%20planning%20to%20relocate%20to%20the%20UAE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20Israel's%20war%20on%20Gaza%20that%20followed%20the%20October%207%20attack%2C%20the%20whole%20Palestinian%20economy%20faced%20the%20consequences.%20Middle%20Frame%20sales%20had%20halted%20completely%20in%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20the%20situation%2C%20I've%20been%20on%20the%20road%20travelling.%20Since%20October%2C%20I've%20been%20in%20Egypt%2C%20Dubai%2C%20Jerusalem%20and%20Ramallah.%20I%20was%20in%20Jordan%20until%20the%20end%20of%20January%2C%20and%20we%20initially%20decided%20to%20focus%20our%20efforts%20on%20the%20Jordanian%20market.%20I%20met%20with%20potential%20clients%2C%20like%20advertising%20and%20news%20agencies%2C%20and%20pitched%20to%20potential%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20don't%20know%20what%20the%20future%20holds.%20We%20took%20a%20risk%20by%20operating%20in%20Ramallah%20for%20nearly%20two%20years%2C%20but%20we%20knew%20we%20should%20acknowledge%20that%20there%20was%20no%20more%20room%20for%20growth%20and%20no%20longer%20risk%20our%20investors'%20money%20in%20a%20market%20filled%20with%20uncertainty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsettler-violence-against-palestinians-west-bank-rights-group-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIsraeli%20settler%20attacks%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20have%20been%20very%20frequent.%20In%20mid-April%2C%20I%20was%20returning%20from%20a%20wedding%20and%20got%20stuck%20in%20a%20village%20for%20hours%20because%20the%20settlers%20were%20blocking%20the%20road.%20That%20was%20the%20same%20night%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firan-israel-drone-strike-biden-administration-strategic-weakness-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIran%20fired%20on%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20it%20really%20hit%20me%20that%20we%20can't%20stay%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20been%20discussing%20whether%20we're%20willing%20to%20relocate.%20We%20know%20that%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsaudi-arabia-vs-uae-middle-east-economic-power-supremacy-dubai-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20UAE%20and%20Saudi%20Arabia%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20bigger%20markets%2C%20and%20we%20think%20the%20UAE%20%E2%80%94%20where%20I%20believe%20there's%20a%20very%20diverse%20business%20market%20%E2%80%94%20would%20be%20the%20best%20place%20for%20us%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20waiting%20on%20news%20from%20a%20local%20investor%2C%20but%20Raya%2C%20our%20CTO%2C%20and%20I%20hope%20to%20relocate%20at%20the%20end%20of%20this%20year.%20Luckily%2C%20Raya's%20husband%20is%20understanding%20and%20open%20to%20moving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20hope%20to%20return%20in%20the%20future%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20had%20started%20%26quot%3BThe%20Middle%20Frame%26quot%3B%20anywhere%20else%2C%20we%20might%20have%20been%20able%20to%20grow%20faster%20and%20raise%20more%20investments%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20regret%20what%20we%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20future%2C%20when%20our%20business%20is%20stable%20in%20a%20different%20market%2C%20we%20could%20maybe%20have%20a%20smaller%20operation%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Palestinian%20startup%20ecosystem%20needs%20more%20examples%20of%20successful%20startups%20in%20the%20wider%20region%20to%20support%20the%20startups%20in%20Palestine%20and%20more%20investment%20bodies%20to%20support%20the%20early-stage%20startups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20the%20Palestinian%20startup%20community%20is%20so%20small%2C%20we've%20had%20to%20get%20on%20calls%20with%20investors%20and%20startup%20founders%20from%20other%20countries%20to%20get%20support%20and%20advice%3B%20it's%20pushed%20us%20to%20make%20connections%20internationally%20and%20it's%20made%20us%20more%20resilient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20taking%20a%20minute%20to%20zoom%20out%20and%20look%20at%20the%20big%20picture%20is%20important.%20Some%20days%2C%20you%20wake%20up%20to%20a%20news%20story%20that%20is%20painful%20to%20see%20and%20hear%2C%20making%20your%20day%2010%20times%20harder%20to%20work%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-palestine-conflict-palestinian-tech-founder-relocate-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714726897000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661e953d10c6b0cde5efdd23%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-palestine-conflict-palestinian-tech-founder-relocate-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Palestinian%20tech%20founder%20shared%20how%20he's%20been%20dealing%20with%20instability%20following%20the%20October%207%20attacks%20in%20Gaza.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ccheong%40insider.com%20(Charissa%20Cheong)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-palestine-conflict-palestinian-tech-founder-relocate-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Many%20Hours%20Should%20You%20Sleep%20Every%20Day%3F%20What%20Research%20Reveals%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3EPeople%20have%20a%20pretty%20intuitive%20sense%20of%20what%20is%20healthy%20%E2%80%93%20standing%20is%20better%20than%20sitting%2C%20exercise%20is%20great%20for%20overall%20health%20and%20getting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fcould-not-getting-enough-sleep-increase-your-risk-of-type-2-diabetes-225179%5C%22%3Egood%20sleep%20is%20imperative%3C%2Fa%3E.%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20exercise%20in%20the%20evening%20may%20disrupt%20our%20sleep%2C%20or%20make%20us%20feel%20the%20need%20to%20be%20more%20sedentary%20to%20recover%2C%20a%20key%20question%20emerges%20%E2%80%93%20what%20is%20the%20best%20way%20to%20balance%20our%2024%20hours%20to%20optimise%20our%20health%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs00125-024-06145-0%5C%22%3EOur%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20attempted%20to%20answer%20this%20for%20risk%20factors%20for%20heart%20disease%2C%20stroke%20and%20diabetes.%20We%20found%20the%20optimal%20amount%20of%20sleep%20was%208.3%20hours%2C%20while%20for%20light%20activity%20and%20moderate%20to%20vigorous%20activity%2C%20it%20was%20best%20to%20get%202.2%20hours%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fdw4bx%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400px%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EFinding%20the%20right%20balance%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrent%20health%20guidelines%20recommend%20you%20stick%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.health.gov.au%2Ftopics%2Fphysical-activity-and-exercise%2Fphysical-activity-and-exercise-guidelines-for-all-australians%2Ffor-adults-18-to-64-years%5C%22%3Esensible%20regime%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20moderate-to%20vigorous-intensity%20physical%20activity%202.5%E2%80%935%20hours%20per%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1016%2Fj.jacc.2019.02.031%5C%22%3Emounting%20evidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.2337%2Fdc14-2073%5C%22%3Esuggests%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20you%20spend%20your%20day%20can%20have%20meaningful%20ramifications%20for%20your%20health.%20In%20addition%20to%20moderate-to%20vigorous-intensity%20physical%20activity%2C%20this%20means%20the%20time%20you%20spend%20sitting%2C%20standing%2C%20doing%20light%20physical%20activity%20(such%20as%20walking%20around%20your%20house%20or%20office)%20and%20sleeping.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20research%20looked%20at%20more%20than%202%2C000%20adults%20who%20wore%20body%20sensors%20that%20could%20interpret%20their%20physical%20behaviours%2C%20for%20seven%20days.%20This%20gave%20us%20a%20sense%20of%20how%20they%20spent%20their%20average%2024%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20start%20of%20the%20study%20participants%20had%20their%20waist%20circumference%2C%20blood%20sugar%20and%20insulin%20sensitivity%20measured.%20The%20body%20sensor%20and%20assessment%20data%20was%20matched%20and%20analysed%20then%20tested%20against%20health%20risk%20markers%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20a%20heart%20disease%20and%20stroke%20risk%20score%20%E2%80%94%20to%20create%20a%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20this%20model%2C%20we%20fed%20through%20thousands%20of%20permutations%20of%2024%20hours%20and%20found%20the%20ones%20with%20the%20estimated%20lowest%20associations%20with%20heart%20disease%20risk%20and%20blood-glucose%20levels.%20This%20created%20many%20optimal%20mixes%20of%20sitting%2C%20standing%2C%20light%20and%20moderate%20intensity%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20looked%20at%20waist%20circumference%2C%20blood%20sugar%2C%20insulin%20sensitivity%20and%20a%20heart%20disease%20and%20stroke%20risk%20score%2C%20we%20noted%20differing%20optimal%20time%20zones.%20Where%20those%20zones%20mutually%20overlapped%20was%20ascribed%20the%20optimal%20zone%20for%20heart%20disease%20and%20diabetes%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EYou're%20doing%20more%20physical%20activity%20than%20you%20think%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20found%20light-intensity%20physical%20activity%20(defined%20as%20walking%20less%20than%20100%20steps%20per%20minute)%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20walking%20to%20the%20water%20cooler%2C%20the%20bathroom%2C%20or%20strolling%20casually%20with%20friends%20%E2%80%93%20had%20strong%20associations%20with%20glucose%20control%2C%20and%20especially%20in%20people%20with%20type%202%20diabetes.%20This%20light-intensity%20physical%20activity%20is%20likely%20accumulated%20intermittently%20throughout%20the%20day%20rather%20than%20being%20a%20purposeful%20bout%20of%20light%20exercise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20experimental%20evidence%20shows%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdiabetesjournals.org%2Fcare%2Farticle%2F39%2F6%2F964%2F29532%2FBenefits-for-Type-2-Diabetes-of-Interrupting%5C%22%3Einterrupting%20our%20sitting%3C%2Fa%3E%20regularly%20with%20light-physical%20activity%20(such%20as%20taking%20a%203%E2%80%935%20minute%20walk%20every%20hour)%20can%20improve%20our%20metabolism%2C%20especially%20so%20after%20lunch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20moderate-to-vigorous%20physical%20activity%20time%20might%20seem%20a%20quite%20high%2C%20at%20more%20than%202%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20we%20defined%20it%20as%20more%20than%20100%20steps%20per%20minute.%20This%20equates%20to%20a%20brisk%20walk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20should%20be%20noted%20that%20these%20findings%20are%20preliminary.%20This%20is%20the%20first%20study%20of%20heart%20disease%20and%20diabetes%20risk%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Coptimal%E2%80%9D%2024%20hours%2C%20and%20the%20results%20will%20need%20further%20confirmation%20with%20longer%20prospective%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20is%20also%20cross-sectional.%20This%20means%20that%20the%20estimates%20of%20time%20use%20are%20correlated%20with%20the%20disease%20risk%20factors%2C%20meaning%20it's%20unclear%20whether%20how%20participants%20spent%20their%20time%20influences%20their%20risk%20factors%20or%20whether%20those%20risk%20factors%20influence%20how%20someone%20spends%20their%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EAustralia's%20adult%20physical%20activity%20guidelines%20need%20updating%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAustralia's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.health.gov.au%2Ftopics%2Fphysical-activity-and-exercise%2Fphysical-activity-and-exercise-guidelines-for-all-australians%2Ffor-adults-18-to-64-years%5C%22%3Ephysical%20activity%20guidelines%3C%2Fa%3E%20currently%20only%20recommend%20exercise%20intensity%20and%20time.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uow.edu.au%2Fmedia%2F2023%2Fwhy-adults-need-to-move-more-stop-sitting-and-sleep-better-.php%5C%22%3Enew%20set%20of%20guidelines%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20being%20developed%20to%20incorporate%2024-hour%20movement.%20Soon%20Australians%20will%20be%20able%20to%20use%20these%20guidelines%20to%20examine%20their%2024%20hours%20and%20understand%20where%20they%20can%20make%20improvements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20our%20new%20research%20can%20inform%20the%20upcoming%20guidelines%2C%20we%20should%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20the%20recommendations%20are%20like%20a%20north%20star%3A%20something%20to%20head%20towards%20to%20improve%20your%20health.%20In%20principle%20this%20means%20reducing%20sitting%20time%20where%20possible%2C%20increasing%20standing%20and%20light-intensity%20physical%20activity%2C%20increasing%20more%20vigorous%20intensity%20physical%20activity%2C%20and%20aiming%20for%20a%20healthy%20sleep%20of%207.5%E2%80%939%20hours%20per%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeneficial%20changes%20could%20come%20in%20the%20form%20of%20reducing%20screen%20time%20in%20the%20evening%20or%20opting%20for%20an%20active%20commute%20over%20driving%20commute%2C%20or%20prioritising%20an%20earlier%20bed%20time%20over%20watching%20television%20in%20the%20evening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20important%20to%20acknowledge%20these%20are%20recommendations%20for%20an%20able%20adult.%20We%20all%20have%20different%20considerations%2C%20and%20above%20all%2C%20movement%20should%20be%20fun.%3Cimg%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F228894%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fchristian-brakenridge-1295221%5C%22%3EChristian%20Brakenridge%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Postdoctoral%20research%20fellow%20at%20Swinburne%20University%2C%20Centre%20for%20Urban%20Transitions%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Fbaker-heart-and-diabetes-institute-974%5C%22%3EBaker%20Heart%20and%20Diabetes%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fhow-much-time-should-you-spend-sitting-versus-standing-new-research-reveals-the-perfect-mix-for-optimal-health-228894%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714726440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F20