2C%20the%20early%20blooming%20of%20rhododendrons%20signals%20a%20concerning%20shift%20in%20climate%20patterns%2C%20disrupting%20ecosystems%2C%20endangering%20local%20traditions%2C%20and%20threatening%20medicinal%20resources.%20This%20premature%20phenomenon%20underscores%20the%20urgent%20need%20for%20conservation%20and%20climate%20action%20to%20safeguard%20both%20nature's%20delicate%20balance%20and%20human%20well-being.%20As%20rhododendrons%20bloom%20out%20of%20season%2C%20they%20serve%20as%20a%20poignant%20reminder%20of%20the%20tangible%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%2C%20urging%20us%20to%20prioritize%20environmental%20stewardship%20for%20future%20generations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20LIFESTYLE%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China's%20true%20military%20spending%20in%202022%20was%20likely%20worth%20%24711%20billion%2C%20or%20'nearly%20equal'%20to%20the%20US%20military%20budget%20that%20year%3A%20US%20think%20tank%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20air%20defense%20squadron%20conducts%20a%20live-fire%20drill%20in%20Changzhou%2C%20Jiangsu%20province%2C%20China%2C%20April%2028%2C%202024.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66347a63ec0c6965690098ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223189%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20air%20defense%20squadron%20conducts%20a%20live-fire%20drill%20in%20Changzhou%2C%20Jiangsu%20province%2C%20China%2C%20April%2028%2C%202024.%3Cp%3ECFOTO%2FFuture%20Publishing%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20new%20report%20says%20China's%20%24229%20billion%20military%20budget%20in%202022%20was%20actually%20equivalent%20to%20%24711%20billion.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20similar%20figure%20was%20touted%20by%20lawmakers%20last%20year%20when%20they%20cited%20US%20intelligence%20estimates.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20report%2C%20by%20think%20tank%20AEI%2C%20breaks%20down%20that%20figure%20to%20show%20where%20China's%20money%20is%20likely%20going%20to.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%202023%2C%20Sen.%20Dan%20Sullivan%20of%20Alaska%20warned%20Congress%20that%20China's%20military%20was%20catching%20up%20to%20America's%20faster%20than%20previously%20imagined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20intelligence%20community%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2F118%2Fcrec%2F2023%2F06%2F01%2F169%2F95%2FCREC-2023-06-01-senate.pdf%23page%3D9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Republican%20senator%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20estimated%20that%20Beijing%20spent%20an%20equivalent%20of%20%24700%20billion%20on%20its%20defense%20budget%20in%202022%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20triple%20its%20reported%20topline%20of%20%24229%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESullivan's%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2Fbill%2F118th-congress%2Fsenate-bill%2F1791%2Fhistory%3Fs%3D2%26r%3D39%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20legislative%20push%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20dig%20further%20into%20the%20matter%20came%20amid%20renewed%20interest%20in%20China's%20true%20military%20budget%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sipri.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2023-04%2F2304_fs_milex_2022.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethink%20tanks%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20observers%20running%20their%20own%20analyses%20of%20Beijing's%20coffers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aei.org%2Fresearch-products%2Freport%2Fkeeping-up-with-the-pacing-threat-unveiling-the-true-size-of-beijings-military-spending%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20Monday%20by%20the%20Washington-based%20American%20Enterprise%20Institute%20seeks%20to%20break%20down%20how%20the%20US%20might%20have%20internally%20reached%20that%20%24700%20billion%20estimation%20for%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report's%20author%2C%20Mackenzie%20Eaglen%2C%20writes%20that%20the%20Chinese%20budget%20is%20worth%20about%20%24711%20billion%20when%20weighed%20against%20America's%2C%20slightly%20higher%20than%20the%20one%20quoted%20in%20June%20by%20Sullivan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20makes%20Beijing's%20spending%20in%202022%20%26quot%3Bnearly%20equal%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20US%20defense%20budget%20of%20about%20%24740%20billion%20that%20year%2C%20wrote%20Eaglen%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20AEI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConsidering%20that%20the%20Pentagon%20has%20labeled%20China%20the%20'pacing%20challenge%2C'%20this%20revelation%20should%20cause%20concern%2C%26quot%3B%20Eaglen%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20mostly%20pieced%20together%20the%20new%20figure%20by%20comparing%20older%20Chinese%20budget%20reports%20and%20spending%20breakdowns%2C%20extrapolating%20them%20onto%20the%20%24229%20billion%20Beijing%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20Chinese%20spending%20reports%20are%20kept%20tightly%20under%20wraps.%20Most%20US%20observers%20haven't%20been%20able%20to%20pin%20the%20%24700%20billion%20on%20hard%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EUnderstanding%20%24711%20billion%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20%24711%20billion%20estimate%20listed%20by%20Eaglen%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20China%20is%20spending%20that%20exact%20amount%20of%20money%20on%20defense.%20Rather%2C%20it%20describes%20the%20purchasing%20power%20of%20its%20military%20budget%20compared%20to%20America's%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-defense-budget-china-undersells-true-military-strength-analysts-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eespecially%20considering%20lower%20wage%20and%20material%20costs%20in%20China.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20a%202020%20Chinese%20report%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdisarmament.unoda.org%2Fconvarms%2Fmilex%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnited%20Nations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Eaglen%20wrote%20that%20China's%202022%20military%20spending%20was%20likely%20divided%20into%20three%20major%20categories%3A%20equipment%2C%20training%20and%20maintenance%2C%20and%20personnel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20purchasing%20power%20parity%20factored%20in%2C%20China%20likely%20spent%20the%20US%20equivalent%20of%20%24135%20billion%20instead%20of%20%2485%20billion%20on%20equipment%20and%20%24121%20billion%20instead%20of%20%2476%20billion%20on%20training%20and%20maintenance%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20biggest%20jump%20comes%20from%20Eaglen's%20estimation%20of%20Chinese%20military%20wages%2C%20which%20typically%20aren't%20publicly%20recorded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLabor%20costs%20are%20demonstrably%20cheaper%20in%20China%2C%20where%20soldiers%20are%20paid%20just%20one-sixteenth%20the%20wage%20of%20a%20US%20Army%20infantryman%2C%26quot%3B%20Eaglen%20wrote%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Fopinion%2Fnational-security%2F4624666-chinas-real-military-budget-has-quietly-become-almost-as-big-as-ours%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopinion%20piece%20for%20The%20Hill.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20report%2C%20she%20compared%20the%20average%20wages%20of%20US%20and%20Chinese%20government%20workers%20and%20found%20that%20the%20former%20are%20paid%204.31%20times%20as%20much%20as%20their%20counterparts%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20that%20factor%2C%20Eaglen%20wrote%20that%20it's%20highly%20likely%20China's%20spending%20on%20personnel%20that%20year%20was%20worth%20%24293%20billion%20of%20US%20military%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there's%20research%20and%20development%2C%20which%20the%20US%20said%20China%20doesn't%20account%20for%20in%20its%20military%20budget%20announcements.%20Eaglen%20estimated%20that%20China%20spent%20about%20%2445%20billion%20on%20R%26amp%3BD%2C%20based%20on%20the%20country%20saying%20it%20spent%20that%20amount%20on%20research%20in%20%26quot%3Bnondisclosed%20agencies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20total%20budget%20comes%20from%20significant%20expenses%20listed%20by%20China%20as%20non-military%2C%20but%20ones%20that%20Eaglen%20argued%20should%20be%20considered%20defense%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20wrote%20that%20one%20such%20expense%20was%20%2445%20billion%20for%20maintaining%20the%20People's%20Armed%20Police%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrutal-training-for-chinas-paramilitary-2016-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparamilitary%20organization%3C%2Fa%3E%20focused%20on%20internal%20security%20but%20tasked%20with%20bolstering%20the%20People's%20Liberation%20Army's%20ranks%20in%20times%20of%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225995%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20serviceman%20uses%20a%20deminer%20to%20detect%20a%20%26quot%3Bminefield%26quot%3B%20during%20an%20explosive%20disposal%20training%20of%20People's%20Armed%20Police%20in%20Nanning%2C%20South%20China's%20Guangxi%20Zhuang%20Autonomous%20region%2C%20May%2016%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6634770f10dfcda409664df2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223997%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20serviceman%20uses%20a%20deminer%20to%20detect%20a%20%26quot%3Bminefield%26quot%3B%20during%20an%20explosive%20disposal%20training%20of%20People's%20Armed%20Police%20in%20Nanning%2C%20South%20China's%20Guangxi%20Zhuang%20Autonomous%20region%2C%20May%2016%2C%202023.%3Cp%3ECFOTO%2FFuture%20Publishing%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20%2445%20billion%20was%20spent%20on%20retirement%2C%20military%20pensions%2C%20and%20demobilization%2C%20%242%20billion%20on%20China's%20Coast%20Guard%2C%20and%20%2421%20billion%20on%20space%20forces%20%E2%80%94%20which%20Eaglen%20calculated%20for%20growth%20based%20on%20an%20official%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignaffairs.house.gov%2Fchina-regional-snapshot-space%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2013%20Chinese%20budget%20of%20%2410.8%20billion%20for%20space%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEqual%20defense%20spending%20between%20the%20United%20States%20and%20China%20plays%20to%20Beijing's%20benefit%2C%26quot%3B%20Eaglen%20wrote%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20US%20defense%20budget%20is%20spread%20across%20various%20theaters%20worldwide%20while%20China%20focuses%20on%20only%20one%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researcher%20called%20on%20the%20US%20to%20provide%20transparency%20on%20its%20findings%20about%20China's%20military%20spending%20power%2C%20citing%20concerns%20that%20the%20%26quot%3BAmerican%20public%20is%20too%20often%20at%20ease%20in%20believing%20the%20US%20military%20remains%20ahead%20of%20all%20its%20competitors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20military%20spending%20is%20also%20often%20cited%20as%20higher%20than%20the%20actual%20defense%20budget.%20Some%20estimates%20for%202023%20are%20as%20high%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fresponsiblestatecraft.org%2F2023%2F05%2F07%2Fgetting-the-defense-budget-right-a-real-grand-total-over-1-4-trillion%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%241.4%20trillion%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewhen%20factoring%20in%20costs%20like%20veterans%20affairs%20spending%2C%20homeland%20security%2C%20security%20for%20international%20affairs%2C%20and%20interest%20accrued%20from%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20US%20in%20March%20passed%20a%20bill%20allocating%20%24825%20billion%20to%20the%20American%20defense%20budget%20in%202024%2C%20the%20smallest%20proportion%20of%20its%20GDP%20since%20World%20War%20II.%20In%20the%20same%20month%2C%20China%20announced%20a%20military%20budget%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globaltimes.cn%2Fpage%2F202403%2F1308188.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24231%20billion%20for%20the%20year.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-military-spending-nearly-equal-us-defense-budget-711-billion-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22publishe