l%20media%20influencer%2C%20a%20midday%20meal%20scam%2C%20the%20mysterious%20demise%20of%20a%20geologist%2C%20an%20attempted%20cover-up%20of%20a%20water%20contamination%20case%20and%2C%20inevitably%2C%20the%20big%20industry%20seeking%20to%20control%20the%20flow%20of%20news%20and%20the%20exercise%20of%20political%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20that%20way%20too%20much%20to%20handle%20in%20a%20single%20season%20of%20a%20series%3F%20It%20perhaps%20is.%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Broken%20News%20S2%3C%2Fi%3E%20is%20at%20times%20undermined%20a%20touch%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20has%20to%20resort%20to%20hurried%20board%20strokes.%20That%20apart%2C%20a%20degree%20of%20confusion%20creeps%20in%20when%20it%20adopts%20simplistic%20methods%20to%20draw%20of%20battle%20lines%20between%20opposing%20worldviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20that%20does%20not%20major%20damage%20to%20the%20overall%20outcome%20it%20is%20because%20the%20script%20ensures%20that%20there%20is%20just%20enough%20happening%20in%20the%20narrative%20at%20a%20pace%20that%20rules%20out%20the%20possibility%20of%20the%20momentary%20snags%20sticking%20out%20and%20slowing%20down%20the%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20follow-up%20to%20the%20Vinay%20Waikul-directed%202022%20newsroom%20drama%20series%2C%20writer%20Sambit%20Mishra%20falls%20back%20on%20newsy%20titbits%20to%20rustle%20up%20an%20intriguing%20story%20that%20touches%20upon%20pertinent%20themes%20with%20the%20seriousness%20that%20they%20merit.%20Not%20that%20all%20of%20it%20hits%20home%20with%20equal%20force%2C%20but%20parts%20of%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Broken%20News%20Season%202%3C%2Fi%3E%20do%20strike%20a%20chord%20and%20provoke%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAided%20by%20strong%20and%20steady%20performances%20from%20the%20lead%20actors%20and%20the%20supporting%20cast%20(Sanjeeta%20Bhattacharya%2C%20Faisal%20Rashid%2C%20Taaruk%20Raina%2C%20Indraneil%20Sengupta%20and%20two%20key%20news%20additions%2C%20Geetika%20Vidya%20Ohlyan%20and%20Akshay%20Oberoi)%2C%20the%20show%20wends%20its%20way%20through%20a%20series%20of%20events%20that%20elicit%20divergent%20responses%20from%20two%20news%20channels%20run%20by%20two%20individuals%20whose%20approaches%20to%20journalism%20are%20diametrically%20opposite.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJostling%20for%20power%2C%20pelf%20and%20position%2C%20the%20journos%20vent%20their%20feelings%20and%20beliefs%20in%20edit%20meetings%20and%20on%20prime%20time%20shows.%20Season%201%20had%20ended%20with%20Radha%20Bhargava%20(Pilgaonkar)%20of%20Awaaz%20Bharati%2C%20a%20channel%20headed%20by%20Amina%20Qureshi%20(Bendre)%2C%20being%20jailed%20after%20Dipankar%20Sanyal%20(Ahlawat)%2C%20editor-in%20chief%20of%20Josh%2024%2F7%20network%2C%20brands%20her%20an%20%26quot%3Banti-national%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHalfway%20through%20the%20opening%20episode%20of%20Season%202%2C%20Radha%20gets%20bail.%20She%20plunges%20right%20back%20into%20her%20ongoing%20tussle%20with%20Dipankar%2C%20who%2C%20on%20his%20part%2C%20does%20not%20budge%20an%20inch%20from%20his%20pursuit%20of%20eyeballs.%20Terms%20like%20'virtue%20signalling'%20and%20'confirmation%20bias'%20are%20heard%20as%20the%20journalists%20debate%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERadha%2C%20young%2C%20uncompromising%20and%20wedded%20to%20a%20cause%2C%20seeks%20to%20harness%20of%20power%20of%20truth%20as%20a%20means%20to%20settling%20scores%20her%20bete%20noire%2C%20the%20man%20responsible%20for%20her%20stint%20in%20prison%20where%20she%20has%20slighted%20and%20tortured%20for%20more%20than%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20process%20of%20trying%20to%20right%20the%20wrongs%20done%20to%20her%2C%20Radha%20appears%20to%20blur%20the%20line%20that%20separates%20the%20journalist%20and%20the%20activist%20in%20her.%20It%20is%20a%20tightrope%20walk.%20There%20is%20a%20price%20to%20pay%20as%20Radha%20opens%20up%20several%20fronts%20and%20plunges%20headlong%20into%20the%20complexities%20of%20a%20multiplicity%20of%20stories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20own%20newsroom%2C%20Radha%20has%20to%20contend%20with%20her%20mentor%20and%20friend%2C%20Amina%2C%20an%20old%20school%20journalist%20who%20swears%20by%20objectivity.%20Those%20who%20speak%20the%20truth%2C%20Amina%20says%2C%20are%20often%20isolated.%20She%20accuses%20Radha%20of%20allowing%20her%20anger%20to%20come%20in%20the%20way%20of%20her%20journalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F2M29LWMXrdA%3Fsi%3DKkJ6KF1_CF8kvOuT%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOutside%20of%20their%20newsroom%20stands%20the%20towering%20and%20pro-establishment%20Dipankar%2C%20who%20brings%20a%20third%20way%20of%20looking%20at%20the%20business%20of%20news.%20TRPs%20mean%20the%20world%20to%20him.%20A%20self-styled%20voice%20of%20the%20nation%2C%20he%20signs%20off%20his%20news%20shows%20with%20%26quot%3B%3Ci%3EYeh%20sawaal%20hai%20desh%20ka%3C%2Fi%3E%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERehana%20Ahmed%20(Ohlyan)%2C%20who%20moves%20from%20reporting%20on%20Bollywood%20stars%20to%20chasing%20hardcore%20news%20and%20anchoring%20shows%2C%20represents%20another%20face%20of%20journalism.%20From%20an%20underprivileged%20background%2C%20work%20is%20a%20daily%20grind%20and%20a%20necessity.%20%26quot%3B%3Ci%3EDeshbhakt%20marne%20tak%3C%2Fi%3E%26quot%3B%20are%20the%20words%20that%20she%20rounds%20off%20her%20shows%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20single%20mother%20struggling%20to%20get%20ahead%20in%20life%20and%20ensure%20that%20her%20son%20secures%20admission%20in%20a%20quality%20school%2C%20Rehana%20frequently%20displeases%20her%20boss%20at%20Josh%2024%2F7%20with%20her%20impulsive%20ways.%20She%20is%20taken%20to%20task%20but%20she%20carries%20on%20regardless.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20there%20is%20Ranjit%20%26quot%3BRonnie%26quot%3B%20Sabharwal%20(Oberoi)%2C%20who%20take